%% Data Flow Diagram - odh-model-controller
%% Generated by: Claude Opus 4.6

sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User / kubectl
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Controller as odh-model-controller<br/>8081/TCP Health<br/>9443/TCP Webhooks
    participant Route as OpenShift Route<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant AuthPolicy as Kuadrant AuthPolicy
    participant EnvoyFilter as Istio EnvoyFilter
    participant NVIDIA as NVIDIA NGC API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant ModelReg as Model Registry<br/>HTTPS/HTTP

    Note over User,ModelReg: Flow 1: InferenceService Reconciliation (RawDeployment)

    User->>K8sAPI: Create InferenceService CR
    K8sAPI->>Controller: Watch event (TLS 1.2+, SA token)
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create Route, ClusterRoleBinding,<br/>metrics Service, ServiceMonitor,<br/>PodMonitor (HTTPS/6443)
    Note right of Controller: TLS Edge or Reencrypt<br/>based on auth annotation

    Note over User,ModelReg: Flow 2: LLMInferenceService Reconciliation (Gateway API)

    User->>K8sAPI: Create LLMInferenceService CR
    K8sAPI->>Controller: Watch event (TLS 1.2+, SA token)
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create AuthPolicy (Gateway-level)<br/>AuthPolicy (HTTPRoute-level)<br/>EnvoyFilter, Role, RoleBinding
    K8sAPI-->>AuthPolicy: AuthPolicy applied to Gateway
    K8sAPI-->>EnvoyFilter: EnvoyFilter applied to Gateway

    Note over User,ModelReg: Flow 3: NIM Account Lifecycle

    User->>K8sAPI: Create NIM Account CR
    K8sAPI->>Controller: Watch event (TLS 1.2+, SA token)
    Controller->>NVIDIA: Validate API key (HTTPS/443,<br/>Bearer token auth)
    NVIDIA-->>Controller: API key valid + model catalog
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create ConfigMap (NIM config),<br/>Secret (pull secret),<br/>Template (ServingRuntime)

    Note over User,ModelReg: Flow 4: Data Connection Secret Aggregation

    User->>K8sAPI: Create labeled Secret<br/>(opendatahub.io/managed=true)
    K8sAPI->>Controller: Watch event (labeled secrets)
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Read data connection Secrets
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create/Update storage-config<br/>Secret (aggregated)

    Note over User,ModelReg: Flow 5: Multi-Node Ray TLS Certificate Management

    K8sAPI->>Controller: Watch event (predictor Pod<br/>with RAY_USE_TLS)
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Read ray-ca-tls Secret (CA cert)
    Note right of Controller: Generate self-signed cert<br/>for Pod IP + SAN DNS
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Update ray-tls Secret<br/>in user namespace
